The diameter is the longest path between any two nodes (may or may not pass through root).

Approach: For each node, the longest path through it = leftHeight + rightHeight.

```
int diameter(Node root) {
  if (root == null) return 0;
  int leftH = height(root.left);
  int rightH = height(root.right);
  return max(leftH + rightH, 
    max(diameter(root.left), diameter(root.right)));
}
```

Optimized: Compute height and diameter in single traversal. Time: O(n)

Use when: Finding subarrays/substrings that satisfy a condition.

Fixed Window:
- Window size is fixed (e.g., max sum of k elements)
- Slide by adding right element, removing left element

Variable Window:
- Window size changes based on condition
- Expand right to include, shrink left to exclude

Template:
```
int left = 0;
for (int right = 0; right < n; right++) {
  // Add arr[right] to window
  while (window condition violated) {
    // Remove arr[left] from window
    left++;
  }
  // Update answer
}
```

Problems: Max sum subarray of size k, Longest substring without repeating characters, Minimum window substring

Use when: Sorted arrays, finding pairs, or partition problems.

Types:
1. Opposite Direction: left=0, right=n-1, move towards center
   - Two Sum in sorted array
   - Container with most water

2. Same Direction: slow and fast pointers
   - Remove duplicates
   - Linked list cycle detection

3. Merge: Two arrays/lists
   - Merge sorted arrays
   - Intersection of arrays

Template (opposite):
```
int left = 0, right = n-1;
while (left < right) {
  if (condition met) return result;
  else if (need more) left++;
  else right--;
}
```

Use when: Need to explore all combinations/permutations/subsets.

Template:
```
void backtrack(state, choices) {
  if (isGoal(state)) {
    addToResult(state);
    return;
  }
  for (choice in choices) {
    if (isValid(choice)) {
      makeChoice(choice);
      backtrack(newState, remainingChoices);
      undoChoice(choice); // backtrack
    }
  }
}
```

Common problems:
- Permutations: Choose from remaining elements
- Combinations: Choose from index onwards (avoid duplicates)
- Subsets: Include or exclude each element
- N-Queens: Place queens row by row, check constraints
- Sudoku: Fill cell by cell, validate board

Optimization: Pruning (skip invalid branches early)
